nodes.text: Tibro was an astronomical object located in the Tibro system, a part of the Baronos sector in the Slice portion of the Colonies. The Human male Beyla Rus was born on Tibro in 24 BBY. Tibro was also the homeworld of the Human female Maxig Kress.

Tibro was first mentioned in the 1993 Star Wars: The Roleplaying Game supplement Wanted by Cracken, which was written by Louis J. Prosperi for West End Games. The 2009 reference book The Essential Atlas placed the Tibro system, and therefore the celestial body Tibro, in grid square N-9.
